               <ce:caption id="cap0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="fspara0010" view="all">(a) Side view and (b) top view of the crystal structure of 2H-MX<ce:inf loc="post">2</ce:inf>. The dashed lines are mirror planes. The inset in (b) represents the Brillouin zone of 2H-MX<ce:inf loc="post">2</ce:inf>. (c) Schematics of K and K’ valleys. The lack of inversion symmetry for the monolayer causes spin-splitting, whereas in the bulk case, the bands are nearly spin-degenerate due to the symmetry.</ce:simple-para>
